description:
build_request() hardcodes using: ["urn:ietf:params:jmap:core", "urn:ietf:params:jmap:chat"] for every request. When blob2, refplus, webpush-vapid, quotas, and chat:websocket capabilities are added, each method must declare only the capabilities it actually uses.

Design: add a using parameter to build_request, or define per-capability using constants:

  const USING_CHAT: &[&str] = &[
      "urn:ietf:params:jmap:core",
      "urn:ietf:params:jmap:chat",
  ];
  const USING_BLOB2: &[&str] = &[
      "urn:ietf:params:jmap:core",
      "urn:ietf:params:jmap:blob2",
  ];
  const USING_QUOTAS: &[&str] = &[...];

Or allow build_request to accept a &[&str] extra_using parameter merged with the core set.

Each method in each module specifies its own using set. Session capability detection (from the session-aware client issue) can guard whether optional capabilities are included.

Tests: assert that a blob2 method call includes urn:ietf:params:jmap:blob2 in the using array.
